5.2	Use Case Descriptions
Use Case no.:  1
Use Case Name:  User profile/authentication
Actors: User, User Management System
Description: 
The user navigates to the registration or login page.
The user enters required credentials (email and password).
The system validates the credentials against stored user data.
If valid, the system creates an authenticated session.
The user is redirected to the dashboard.


Alternate Path: The user may update profile information (username, theme preference) from the profile settings page.

Exception Path: If credentials are invalid or the email already exists during registration, an error message is displayed.

Pre-condition:
 User must provide valid registration information
The system must have access to the Users database

Post-condition: User is successfully logged in and redirected to the dashboard, or an error message is displayed.


Use Case no.:  2
Use Case Name:  Create playlist from description
Actors: User, Core System, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user navigates to “Create Playlist from Description” on the dashboard.
The user enters a natural language description of a mood or scenario.
The system processes the description using the LLM module.
The system queries relevant songs using audio features and mood tags.
A generated playlist is displayed to the user.
The user chooses to save or discard the playlist.

Alternate Path: The user may modify the description and regenerate the playlist.

Exception Path: If the description cannot be processed or no matching songs are found, an error message is displayed.

Pre-condition:
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in

Post-condition: A playlist is generated and either saved to the user’s library or discarded.


Use Case no.:  3
Use Case Name:  Generate playlist from user listening history
Actors: User, User Management System, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user selects the “Generate playlist from history” button on the dashboard
The system uses the id of the user to grab their listening history
Listening history is used by the Audio Analytics System to generate a playlist with tracks related to the user’s history
The playlist “Your History Playlist #” is added to the user’s library, and a success message is displayed
The user is redirected to their library of playlists
Alternate Path: The user may choose to discard the generated playlist instead of adding it to their library
Exception Path: If the user does not have any listening history, a playlist will not be generated, and an error will be displayed

Pre-condition: 
User must have a valid account
User must have a listening history
User must be logged in
Post-condition: Playlist is generated based on user listening history, and the user is sent to their library of playlists

Use Case no.:  4
Use Case Name:  Export playlist
Actors: User, Spotify API, External Tools Integration
Description: 
The user navigates to the playlist library on the dashboard
The user selects a playlist from their library
The user clicks the “Export Playlist” button
The playlist is created on the user’s Spotify account using the Spotify API, and a success message is displayed
The user is returned to their playlist library
Alternate Path: None
Exception Path: If the user does not have a Spotify account connected, an error is displayed prompting them to connect one
Pre-condition: 
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
System must be given access to the user’s Spotify account
Post-condition: Playlist is successfully created on the Spotify account connected to the user’s profile, and the user is returned to their library of playlists




Use Case no.:  5
Use Case Name:  Collaborate on playlist
Actors: User, Core System, Playlist Versioning Manager
Description: 
The user navigates to a playlist they own.


The user enables collaborative mode.


The user invites another registered user to collaborate.


The invited user accepts the collaboration request.


Both users may add or remove songs from the playlist.


Changes are tracked and saved as playlist versions.

Alternate Path: The playlist owner may assign different permission levels (view-only or edit).

Exception Path: If the invited user does not have a valid account, an error is displayed.

Pre-condition:
User must be logged in
Playlist must exist
The invited user must have a valid account

Post-condition: The playlist becomes collaborative, and authorized users may edit it.


Use Case no.:  6
Use Case Name:  Receive notifications
Actors: User, Core System
Description: 
A system event occurs (playlist invite, export success, collaboration change).


The system generates a notification for the affected user.


The notification is stored in the Notifications table.


The user is alerted via the dashboard interface.


The user views and optionally marks the notification as read.

Alternate Path: The user may disable certain notification types in settings.

Exception Path: If notification storage fails, the system logs the error but continues core operations.



Pre-condition:
User must have a valid account
A triggering system event must occur

Post-condition: The user is informed of the event, and the notification status is updated.
Use Case no.:  7
Use Case Name:  Compare playlists
Actors: User, Core System, Playlist Versioning Manager, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user navigates to either their own playlist or the playlist of another user
The user clicks the “Compare” button on the playlist page
The user is displayed a list of the playlists in their library and must choose which playlist to compare to
The playlists are compared by the Audio Analytics System
The user is provided a report detailing similarities and differences between the two selected playlists
Alternate Path: None
Exception Path: If the user does not have any of their own playlists to compare to, an error is displayed prompting them to create a playlist to use the comparison function
Pre-condition: 
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
User must have a valid playlist to compare to
Post-condition: A report comparing the two playlists selected by the user is displayed, and when closed, the user is returned to the playlist page from step 1

Use Case no.:  8
Use Case Name:  Manage friends
Actors: User, Core System, User Management System
Description: 
The user navigates to the “Friends” section on the dashboard.
The user searches for another user by username or email.
The user clicks “Add Friend” to send a friend request.
The system records the request in the Friendships table with status PENDING.
The receiving user is notified of the incoming friend request.
The receiving user can choose to accept or decline the request.
If accepted, the friendship status is updated to ACCEPTED, and both users appear in each other’s friends list.
The user can also choose to Remove Friend, which deletes the friendship record from the database.
Alternate Path: The receiving user declines the friend request. The system removes the pending request, and no friendship is created. 
Exception Path: If the user searches for a username that does not exist, the system displays an error message indicating that the user could not be found.
Pre-condition: 
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
Post-condition: A friendship relationship is created, updated, or removed depending on the user’s action, and the friends list is updated accordingly. 

Use Case no.:  9
Use Case Name:  View trending songs
Actors: User, Core System
Description: 
User navigates to the “Trending Songs” section on the dashboard
The page is populated with a ranked list of the top 50 currently trending songs
Alternate Path: None
Exception Path: If the trending score of any two or more songs is the same, those songs will be ordered alphabetically
Pre-condition: 
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
Post-condition: The user is provided with a ranked list of the top 50 currently trending songs

Use Case no.:  10
Use Case Name:  View user music preference analytics
Actors: User, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user navigates to the “Music Preference Analytics” section.
The system retrieves aggregated listening history data.
The system displays summaries such as top genres, total playtime, and trends over selected timeframes.
The user may filter analytics by timeframe (week, month, year).
The analytics dashboard updates dynamically based on selection.
Alternate Path: If no timeframe is selected, the system defaults to the most recent week.

Exception Path: If no listening history exists, the system displays a message indicating insufficient data.

Pre-condition:
 User must have a valid account
User must be logged in

Post-condition: The user is presented with a detailed analytics dashboard reflecting their music preferences.

Use Case no.:  11
Use Case Name:  Tag Songs with Mood Descriptors
Actors: User, Core System, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user navigates to a song page or playlist.
The user selects the option to add mood descriptors to a song.
The user chooses one or more mood tags (e.g., happy, calm, energetic).
The system validates and records the selected mood descriptors.
The tagged data is stored and used by the Audio Analytics System to improve recommendations and playlist generation.
Alternate Path: The user may remove or modify existing mood descriptors for the song

Exception Path: If the song does not exist in the system database, an error message is displayed.

Pre-condition:
 User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
Song must exist in the system

Post-condition: Mood descriptors are successfully associated with the song and stored in the database






Use Case no.:  12
Use Case Name:  Rename playlist
Actors: User, Core System
Description: 
The user navigates to their playlist library.
The user selects a playlist they own.
The user clicks the “Rename Playlist” option.
The user enters a new name for the playlist.
The system validates the new name and updates the playlist record.
The updated name is displayed in the user’s library. 
Alternate Path: The user cancels the rename operation before saving.

Exception Path: If the new playlist name is invalid or empty, the system displays an error message.

Pre-condition:
 User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
Playlist must exist and belong to the user

Post-condition: 
The playlist name is successfully updated in the system.

Use Case no.:  13
Use Case Name: Toggle System theme
Actors: User, Core System
Description: 
The user navigates to the profile settings page.
The user selects the option to change the system theme.
The user toggles between available themes (e.g., light mode or dark mode).
The system saves the theme preference in the user profile.
The interface immediately updates to reflect the selected theme. 
Alternate Path: The user may revert to the previous theme before saving.
Exception Path: If the theme preference cannot be saved due to a system error, the system displays an error message and retains the previous theme.

Pre-condition:
 User must have a valid account
User must be logged in

Post-condition: The user’s theme preference is updated and applied across the system.
Use Case no.:  14
Use Case Name: Rate and review songs
Actors: User, Core System
Description: 
The user navigates to a song page.
The user selects the option to rate the song.
The user provides a rating (e.g., 1–5 stars) and optionally writes a review.
The system validates and stores the rating and review.
The rating contributes to the song’s overall average rating displayed to users. 
Alternate Path: The user may edit or delete their previously submitted rating or review.

Exception Path: If the rating value is outside the valid range, the system displays an error message.

Pre-condition:
 User must have a valid account
User must be logged in
Song must exist in the system

Post-condition: The rating and review are successfully recorded and associated with the user.



Use Case no.:  15
Use Case Name: Generate profile analytics
Actors: User, Core system, Audio Analytics System
Description: 
The user navigates to the profile analytics section.
The system retrieves user activity data, including playlists, listening history, and interactions.
The Audio Analytics System processes the data to generate insights.
The system displays analytics such as most played songs, favorite artists, listening patterns, and playlist activity.
The user may explore different visualizations or filters. 
Alternate Path: The user may export analytics summaries as a report.

Exception Path: If insufficient data exists to generate analytics, the system displays a message indicating that more activity is required.

Pre-condition:
User must have a valid account
User must be logged in

Post-condition: The user is presented with a detailed analytics view of their profile activity and music behavior.
